===Etymology===
From [[motor]] + [[bicycle]]. 

From Webster's New International Dictionary Second Edition:
:'''motorcycle'''
:n. A two-wheeled automotive vehicle having one or two riding saddles and sometimes having a third wheel for the support of a sidecar.  In Great Britain the term motorcycle is treated by statute (3 Edw. VII. C36) as limited to motorcars (self propelled vehicles) designed to travel on not more than three wheels, and weighing unladen (that is without water, fuel, or accumulators necessary for propulsion) not more than three hundred weight (336 lbs).

:'''motorcycle'''  (V. I.)
To ride a motorcycle or go by motorcycle -
:'''motorcyclist''' n.

